Parios: Archilochus was born at Paros, though he lived a roving life. Though not strictly speaking the inventor of the iambic metre (Mahaffy Greek Lz'ccratme 1. 157) he was the first to use it largely in literature. But he also employed the elegiae verse, introduced shortly before his time by Callinus.
